## Conditionals (if-else)

Syntax:

```
if [ condition ]
then
    command
else
    command
fi
```

Example:

```
a=10
if [ $a -gt 5 ]
then
    echo "greater"
else
    echo "smaller"
fi
```

### Practice (if-else)

1.

```
read num
if [ $num -gt 0 ]
then
    echo "positive"
else
    echo "negative"
fi
```

2.

```
read a
read b
if [ $a -eq $b ]
then
    echo "equal"
else
    echo "not equal"
fi
```

3.

```
read name
if [ "$name" = "admin" ]
then
    echo "welcome admin"
else
    echo "user"
fi
```

